        "The user–movie interaction matrix is the core data structure for the item-based collaborative\n",
        "filtering model. Rows represent users, columns represent movies, and each cell contains the\n",
        "mean rating given by that user to that movie. Missing values (the vast majority of cells) are\n",
        "filled with zero to enable cosine similarity computation.\n"
