        "## 5. Cosine Similarity Between Movies\n",
        "\n",
        "Cosine similarity quantifies the directional alignment between two item rating vectors.\n",
        "For movies *i* and *j*: `sim(i, j) = (v_i · v_j) / (||v_i|| × ||v_j||)`, yielding values\n",
        "in [0, 1]. This is computed for all item pairs using `sklearn.metrics.pairwise.cosine_similarity`\n",
        "applied to the transposed user–movie matrix, producing a 9,724 × 9,724 item similarity matrix.\n"
      ],
      "id": "LDuXzPAwTjjJ"
    },
